    "course_title": "HUMAN SEXUALITY: SOCIAL AND PSYCHOLOGICAL ISSUES",
    "description": "Biological, psychological and sociological aspects of sexual relationships and behavior. Presents theoretical and empirical materials on sexuality throughout the life-course, including childhood, adolescence, adulthood, and later life. Attention is given to gender, religion, education and the law as they relate to sexual expression in society.",
